# Documentation Update Requirement

When modifying any Python code in this project, you MUST update the documentation files to reflect the changes:

## Files to Update

1. **README.md** - Explains how to use the bot
   - Update usage instructions if behavior changes
   - Add/remove/modify examples as needed
   - Update configuration options if applicable

2. **IMPLEMENTATION.md** - Explains the implementation, design, and flow
   - Update design descriptions if architecture changes
   - Modify flow diagrams or explanations if logic changes
   - Document new classes, methods, or patterns introduced

## Checklist

After every code change:
- [ ] Review if README.md needs updates (user-facing changes)
- [ ] Review if IMPLEMENTATION.md needs updates (internal changes)
- [ ] Ensure documentation matches the current state of the code
